Dear Bruno,

Thank you for the defect report. I wasn&#39;t able to reproduce exactly the same
behavior you describe, but JUnit 3 tests don&#39;t work exactly the same as they
did before. For example:

public class CastToTestTest {
    public static class Example implements junit.framework.Test {
        public int countTestCases() {
            return 0;
        }
        public void run(TestResult result) {
            // do nothing
        }
        public static junit.framework.Test suite() {
            TestSuite result= new TestSuite();
            result.addTest(new Example());
            return result;
        }
    }
    @Test public void runTestWhichIsNotATestCase() {
        // Doesn&#39;t compile: TestRunner.run(Example.class);
        TestResult result= TestRunner.run(Example.suite());
        assertTrue(result.wasSuccessful());
    }
}

The first line of the test doesn&#39;t compile, which seems like an error to me,
but the test itself passes without a class cast exception. Did I
misunderstand your report?

Regards,

Kent Beck
